# Folder Structure (Hard Rules)

- Follow the existing Next.js **app router** conventions.
- **URLs** in `app/` are lowercase with hyphens.
- Place files consistently:
  - `components/ui/` — shadcn/ui and base UI elements.
  - `components/providers/` — all providers (context/state).
  - `components/icons/` — icons by file; export via `components/icons/index.ts`.
  - `components/wrappers/` — global/page wrappers (e.g., Navbar/Title wrappers).
  - `components/views/<page>/` — page-specific components; break large ones into
    smaller parts in the same folder.
  - `components/common/` — reusable components shared across pages.
  - `components/cards/` — reusable card components.
- Outside `components/`:
  - `config/site.ts` — navbar/footer/meta data.
  - `hooks/` — custom hooks.
  - `styles/` — CSS.
  - `lib/` — utils, `cn`, fonts, clients (Stripe, Supabase).
- `tsconfig.json`:
  - Define path aliases; **do not** create aliases for individual pages (except
    Home if already configured).
